description._content: TITLE West Street, Keene, NH CREATOR SUBJECT Streets - NH - Keene Buildings - NH - Keene Elms - NH - Keene DESCRIPTION Photograph of West Street, located in Keene New Hampshire, showing the Faulkner and Colony Manufacturing Company buildings. First called Piety Lane and then Pleasant Street, it was also known at one time as Mill Street, probably due to the extensive area covered by Faulkner & Colony Mfg. Co. Laid out about 1740, this early route left Main Street and then turned northwesterly across house lots now on the south side of West Street and entered the present West at the corner of School Street. It passed "Maccany Plain", on which West Keene is built, in its course over West Hill to Chesterfield. The Keene Electric Railway had a car line over this street to West Keene. Until the bypass was completed in 1966, West Street received some of the heaviest traffic through Keene. PUBLISHER Keene Public Library DATE DIGITAL 20080421 DATE ORIGINAL 1900?-1920?
